	<div class="About Us" id="AboutUs">
	<h2>About Us</h2>
		At City Hospital, the Division of Obstetrics and Gynaecology, 
		generally known as the obs/gyn specialty, includes the two subspecialties of gynaecology and obstetrics. 
		We specialise in prenatal and postnatal care for women, as well as the diagnosis and treatment of illnesses 
		of the female reproductive organs. Other women's health issues addressed include menopause, hormone issues, 
		contraception (birth control), and infertility. In a "patient first" environment, the speciality is known for 
		providing comprehensive, compassionate, sophisticated, and committed care.
	</div>
	<br><br>
	<div class="What we Treat" id="WhatweTreat?">
	<h2>What we Treat?</h2>
		At our Obstetrics and Gynaecology Division at City Hospital, we invest our efforts, 
		time, and expertise to help patients diagnose and treat all kinds of disorders associated with 
		obstetrics and gynaecological needs of women.
	<br>
		<ul type="square">
<li>Asherman's Syndrome
<li>Gestational Diabetes
<li>Ectopic Pregnancy
<li>Haemolytic Disease of the New-born
<li>Labour and its Abnormalities
<li>Abruptio Placentae
<li>Polycystic Ovarian Syndrome (PCOS)
<li>Genital Tract Infections
<li>Fetal Abnormalities
<li>Gynaecological Oncology
		</ul>
	</div>
	<br><br>
	<div class="How we Treat" id="HowweTreat?">
	<h2>How we Treat?</h2>
	Combining a skilled pool of doctors with the latest technology, 
	the division of Obstetrics and Gynaecology aims at providing advanced 
	care and treatment to all the women at affordable prices. The division is considered 
	an advanced centre for diagnosis and treatment of all types of obstetrics and gynaecological 
	diseases with a conservative or operative approach.
	</div>
